For anyone else struggling with Chrome not automatically updating on changing index.js, here's a solution/workaround.

React has a new-ish feature called Fast Refresh. I can't quite tell if this is intentional or not but it seems to completely ignore changes to index.js until a manual refresh. The two main ways to fix this are to turn off Fast Refresh by creating a file named ".env" containing "FAST_REFRESH=false", or to make index.js just more boilerplate by making it contain just something like

import ReactDOM from 'react-dom';
import App from './App';
ReactDOM.render(<App />, document.getElementById('root'));

and moving all the actual code to App.js.

